en.PPU_MARKUP_DESC: You can top up without power and geographical limits, and without having to pay an activation fee or incur other fixed costs.
en.PPU_MARKUP_FEAT1_DESC: The network is present in 29 European countries, and is constantly expanding. It currently has more than 370,000 charging points.
en.PPU_MARKUP_FEAT2_DESC: Thanks to the network, not only can you recharge wherever you are, but you can manage all the activities related to recharging your electric or plug-in hybrid car with a single app.
en.PPU_MARKUP_FEAT3_DESC: eSolutions implements a CO2 compensation plan, guaranteeing zero-impact electric charging and attentive to the protection of the planet.
en.PPU_FIXFEE_DESC: With a monthly fee, you can recharge without geographical and power limits at better prices than those offered for each recharge point.
en.PPU_FIXFEE_FEAT1_DESC: The network is present in 29 European countries, and is constantly expanding. It currently has more than 370,000 charging points.

en.ECP_DESC: The solution to integrate your company car fleet into electric mobility and offer on-the-go charging as a benefit to your employees.
en.ECP_SPECS_1: Registration and activation of the account by the employee with the code received from the company.
en.ECP_SPECS_2: Vehicle charging by the employee via dedicated app or RFID card.
en.ECP_SPECS_3: Monthly billing to the company with activation charge, monthly fees and employee consumption.

en.EPAL_02: Would you like to report a problem?
en.EPAL_DESC_100:
Check if the eProWallbox circuit breaker is ON.
Check that the CN1 cabling is correct. Check the voltage in CN1.
en.EPAL_DESC_101: Disconnect the Type 2 cable, wait for the temperature to fall, then the error will clear itself. In order to restart the charging session, plug in the cable again. Make sure that the installation site is compatible with the temperature range (-25°C/+50°C without direct exposure to sunlight).
en.EPAL_TITLE_102: Communication error between MCU and MPU
en.EPAL_DESC_102: Restart the eProWallbox from the circuit breaker, leaving the eProWallbox switched off for at least 60 seconds.
en.EPAL_TITLE_103: Hardware fault, ground protection device error. (GPD error)
en.EPAL_TITLE_104: Hardware fault, residual current monitor AC error. (RCM AC trip)
en.EPAL_DESC_104: Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable).
en.EPAL_TITLE_105: Hardware fault, residual current monitor DC error. (RCM DC trip)
en.EPAL_DESC_105: Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable).
en.EPAL_DESC_106: Restart the eProWallbox from the circuit breaker, leaving the eProWallbox switched off for at least 60 seconds.
en.EPAL_DESC_107:
Check that the Modbus configuration on the DPM PowerMeter device is correct, as described in the manual.
Check the Modbus communication cable wiring on CN12, as described in the manual. Check that the communication cable used is suitable for Modbus RS485.
Check that the DPM model configuration on PowerUp is correct.
en.EPAL_TITLE_108: Configuration Error, Rotary switch position (supply tye) is not consistent with the DPM/MID type
en.EPAL_DESC_108:
Check the position of the rotary switch. If it is not consistent with the 1-ph/3-ph installation, change it according to the table in the manual, then restart the wallbox.
If the accessories (DPM/MID) are not installed, make sure that the function is disabled in PowerUp. If the accessories (DPM/MID) are installed, check that the correct model is selected on the PowerUp. Then restart the wallbox.
en.EPAL_DESC_109:
Check the configuration of the master/slave set up from PowerUp
Check that the Master wallbox is available
Check that the wiring of the Modbus communication cable on CN9 and CN10 is as described in the manual.
Check that the communication cable used is suitable for Modbus RS485.
en.EPAL_DESC_110:
Check that the Modbus configuration on the MIDcounter device is correct, as described in the manual. Check the Modbus communication cable wiring on CN12, as described in the manual.
Check that the communication cable used is suitable for Modbus RS485
Check that the MID model configuration on PowerUp is correct.
en.EPAL_TITLE_300: Inconsistency between the wallbox contactor command and feedback
en.EPAL_DESC_300: Restart the eProWallbox from the circuit breaker, leaving the eProWallbox switched off for at least 60 seconds.
en.EPAL_TITLE_301: Short circuit detected on the Control Pilot line
en.EPAL_DESC_301:
With the device switched off, check that there are is damage and no defects inside and outside the socket (if so avoid using the dispositivo and contact Customer Service).
Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable)
en.EPAL_TITLE_302: State E or F set on the Control Pilot line
en.EPAL_DESC_302:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet.
Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable)
en.EPAL_DESC_303:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet.
Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable)
en.EPAL_DESC_304:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet. Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related, attempt a new charging session (if possible with another cable)
en.EPAL_DESC_305:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet. Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related, attempt a new charging session (if possible with another cable)
en.EPAL_TITLE_306: Diode fault detected on Control Pilot line (no -12V).
en.EPAL_DESC_306: Attempt a new charging session unplugging and reinserting the cable from both the dispositivo and vehicle inlet.
en.EPAL_DESC_307:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet.
Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possi- ble with another vehicle or another cable)
en.EPAL_TITLE_308: Incoherency between motor command and feedback, or motor in error state.
en.EPAL_DESC_308:
Attempt a new charging session unplugging and reinserting the cable from both the dispositivo and vehicle inlet.
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet.
en.EPAL_TITLE_309: Motor check error during EVSE initialization phase.
en.EPAL_DESC_309: Restart the eProWallbox from the circuit breaker, leaving the eProWallbox switched off for at least 60 seconds.
en.EPAL_TITLE_310: Error detected before charging (PP not detected, or motor fault, or CP not detected).
en.EPAL_DESC_310:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet. Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possible with another vehicle or another cable).
en.EPAL_TITLE_311: Hardware check error detected after charging (motor fault, or CP not disconnected).
en.EPAL_DESC_311:
With the device switched off, check that there is no damage and no defects inside and outside the cable and its connectors (if so avoid using it and attempt charge with another cable).
Check that the cable connectors are fully inserted inside the dispositivo socket and vehicle inlet. Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related and attempt another charging session (if possible with another vehicle or another cable).
en.EPAL_TITLE_312: Emergency stop received from the MPU.
en.EPAL_DESC_312: Restart the eProWallbox from the circuit breaker, leaving the eProWallbox switched off for at least 60 seconds.
en.EPAL_TITLE_313: Current detected during charging, with 100% duty cycle on the Control Pilot line
en.EPAL_DESC_313: Check that the problem is not cable nor vehicle related, attempt a new charging session with another cable and/or dispositivo.
en.EPAL_TITLE_315: Current over limit on phase L1
en.EPAL_DESC_315: Unplug the cable, if possible lower the power of charge on the vehicle side and attempt a new charging session.
en.EPAL_TITLE_316: Current over limit on phase L2
en.EPAL_DESC_316: Unplug the cable, if possible lower the power of charge on the vehicle side and attempt a new charging session.
en.EPAL_TITLE_317: Current over limit on phase L3
en.EPAL_DESC_317: Unplug the cable, if possible lower the power of charge on the vehicle side and attempt a new charging session.
en.EPAL_TITLE_318: Voltage below a threshold on phase L1
en.EPAL_DESC_318:
The rotary switch is in a three-phase position. Check that the intended installation in three-phase. If not, select the correct rotary switch position as per Installation Manual.
Check that the voltage on CN1-R is above 196 V. If the voltage is below 196 V, check the electric system or contact the energy supplier.
en.EPAL_TITLE_319: Voltage below a threshold on phase L2
en.EPAL_DESC_319:
The rotary switch is in a three-phase position. Check that the intended installation in three-phase. If not, select the correct rotary switch position as per Installation Manual.
Check that the voltage on CN1-S is above 196 V. If the voltage is below 196 V, check the electric system or contact the energy supplier.
en.EPAL_TITLE_320: Voltage below a threshold on phase L3
en.EPAL_DESC_320:
Check the rotary switch position is consistent with 1-ph/3-ph installation following the table in the installation manual.
Check that the voltage on CN1-T is above 196 V. If the voltage is below 196 V, check the electric system or contact the energy supplier.
en.EPAL_TITLE_400: State A detected on the Control Pilot line in pilot simplified case (could be an EV normal stop)
en.EPAL_DESC_InternalError: Error in internal hard- or software component.
en.EPAL_DESC_LocalListConflict: The authorization information received from the Central System is in conflict with the LocalAuthorizationList.
en.EPAL_DESC_ConnectorLockFailure: Failure to lock or unlock connector.
en.EPAL_DESC_EvCommunicationError: Communication failure with the vehicle, might be Mode 3 or other communication protocol problem. This is not a real error in the sense that the Charge Point doesn’t need to go to the faulted state. Instead, it should go to the SuspendedEVSE state.
en.EPAL_DESC_WeakSignal: Wireless communication device reports a weak signal.
en.EPAL_DESC_OtherError: Other type of error. More information in vendorErrorCode.
en.EPAL_DESC_GroundFailure: Ground fault circuit interrupter has been activated.
en.EPAL_DESC_HighTemperature: Temperature inside Charge Point is too high.
en.EPAL_DESC_OverCurrentFailure: Over current protection device has tripped.
en.EPAL_DESC_OverVoltage: Voltage has risen above an acceptable level.
en.EPAL_DESC_UnderVoltage: Voltage has dropped below an acceptable level.
